  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (inadequate-metrics variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation results report aggregate RMSE and R^2 across all five flow-speed operating points, which appear to demonstrate strong model fidelity; however, the COU's actual question of interest is identification of the single worst-case operating condition (maximum relative hemolysis index), and aggregate goodness-of-fit metrics do not capture whether the model correctly rank-orders or bounds that extremum.",
